display.description: 20g dose, 55g yield.  8 mL/s water flow until 35g, then freezes piston for remaining espresso to flow as a result of depressurization. Last 20-25g is slow. Consider other water flow rates. Lower will need finer grind or longer duration, vice versa for higher. Target grind is coarse enough to not trigger the pressure limit (1.0 bar) but fine enough to get to the target yield.
